com.cortxt.app.corelib.Utils

Class QosInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cortxt.app.corelib.Utils.QosInfo

  • public class QosInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    QosInfo is a class that consolidates a wide variety of information about the network state of the phone. The information originated from several sources such as apis, listeners, hidden methods and possibly even service mode. QosInfo contains 4 inner classes representing the main network types, and each is only populated if in that network type
    • GSMInfo
    • WiFiInfo
    • LTEInfo
    • CDMAInfo
    • plus general info in main class

    Since:
    1.0

      class  QosInfo.GSMInfo
      GSMInfo exposes information relevant to 2G GSM Networks such as GPRS and EDGE LAC CellID RSSI ECI0 (Ec/n0)
      class  QosInfo.LTEInfo
      LTEInfo exposes information relevant to LTE Networks RSSI RSRP (main signal indicator) RSRQ SNR (main quality indicator) Base Station Identifiers Tac Ci Pci SNR
      class  QosInfo.NetworkInfo
      NetworkInfo is meant to be used directly to simplify access to information about the connected network.
      class  QosInfo.WCDMAInfo
      WCDMAInfo exposes information relevant to 3G Networks such as UMTS and HSDPA LAC RNC CellID PSC RSCP ECI0 (Ec/n0) SNR
      class  QosInfo.WIFIInfo
      WIFIInfo exposes information relevant to WiFi Networks RSSI (main signal indicator) (no quality indicator) Base Station Identifiers WifiID

      • connectedNetwork

        public QosInfo.NetworkInfo connectedNetwork
        The connectedNetwork represents the network that is currently connected, whether it be LTE, WiFi etc.. As a NetworkInfo object, it can be used in a unified way to access relevant info about the network. For example: If CDMA, LTE and WiFi are active at the same time, the connectedNetwork is WiFi, because that is the only network in use for data connections.
